1.The nohup command is used to run another command in the background without hanging up, meaning it keeps running even after you log out or close the terminal.

sheroon$ nohup python3 my_script.py > output.log 2>&1 &

> output.log → Redirects standard output to output.log.

2>&1 → Redirects standard error to standard output.

& → Runs it in the background.

